dy regarding water loss;</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="11" slineno="0-11" level="1">requires the division to report the findings of the study;</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="12" slineno="0-12" level="1">imposes a repeal date; and</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="13" slineno="0-13" level="1">makes technical and conforming amendments.</hl></hp><moni numlevel="1" lineno="14" slineno="0-14" display="none">Money Appropriated in this Bill:</moni><moniNone lineno="15">None</moniNone><oc numlevel="1" lineno="16" slineno="0-16">Other Special Clauses:<ocl type="effdate" sort="2" numlevel="1" lineno="17" slineno="0-17">This bill provides a special effective date.</ocl></oc><sa numlevel="1" lineno="18" slineno="0-18">Utah Code Sections Affected:<saamd numlevel="1" lineno="19" slineno="0-19"><snhead>AMENDS:</snhead><sn num="63I-2-273" src="code" uid="C63I-2-S273_2026050620260506" buid="3" sort="63I02 02730020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="20" slineno="0-20"><bold>63I-2-273</bold><parens><paren sort="00" type="original" show="true" display="space"><effect>Effective </effect><date>05/06/26</date></paren><paren sort="00" type="original" show="true"><effect>Superseded </effect><date>07/01/26</date></paren></parens> , as last amended by Laws of Utah <ln numlevel="1" lineno="21" slineno="0-21"/>2024, Third Special Session, Chapter 5</sn><sn num="63I-2-273" src="code" uid="C63I-2-S273_2026070120260701" buid="4" sort="63I02 02730020260701" numlevel="1" lineno="22" slineno="0-22"><bold>63I-2-273</bold><parens><paren sort="00" type="original" show="true"><effect>Effective </effect><date>07/01/26</date></paren></parens> , as last amended by Laws of Utah 2025, Chapter 124</sn></saamd><saent numlevel="1" lineno="23" slineno="0-23"><snhead>ENACTS:</snhead><sn num="73-10-32.7" src="code" uid="C73-10-S32.7_2026050620260506" buid="1" sort="73 10 00320720260506" numlevel="1" lineno="24" slineno="0-24"><bold>73-10-32.7</bold><parens><paren sort="00" type="original" show="true"><effect>Effective </effect><date>05/06/26</date></paren></parens> , Utah Code Annotated 1953</sn></saent></sa></lt><enacthead lineno="25"/><enact numlevel="1" lineno="26" slineno="0-26">Be it enacted by the Legislature of the state of Utah:</enact><bdy><bsec buid="3" num="63I-2-273" type="amend" src="code" uid="C63I-2-S273_2026050620260506" sort="63I02 02730020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="27" slineno="1-1" sn="1"><section number="63I-2-273" numlevel="1" lineno="28" slineno="1-2" type="amend"><secline lineno="27">Section 1. Section <bold>63I-2-273</bold> is amended to read:</secline><catline lineno="28"><bold>63I-2-273<parens><paren sort="00" type="original" show="true" display="space"><effect>Effective </effect><date>05/06/26</date></paren><paren sort="00" type="original" show="true"><effect>Superseded </effect><date>07/01/26</date></paren></parens>. Repeal dates: Title 73.</bold></catline><sectionText lineno="29"><tab/><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="3" groupid="3" style="2" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" deltag="both">Reserved</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="2" groupid="2" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="73-10-32.7">73-10-32.7</xref>, Study regarding water losses, is repealed July 1, 2027</amend>.</sectionText></section></bsec><bsec buid="4" num="63I-2-273" type="amend" src="code" uid="C63I-2-S273_2026070120260701" sort="63I02 02730020260701" numlevel="1" lineno="30" slineno="2-1" sn="2"><section number="63I-2-273" numlevel="1" lineno="31" slineno="2-2" type="amend"><secline lineno="30">Section 2. Section <bold>63I-2-273</bold> is amended to read:</secline><catline lineno="31"><bold>63I-2-273<parens><paren sort="00" type="original" show="true"><effect>Effective </effect><date>07/01/26</date></paren></parens>. Repeal dates: Title 73.</bold></catline><subsection ssid="4-1" dnum="_-o:1-i" numlevel="1" lineno="32" slineno="2-3" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1" placement="noreturn"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1000" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(1)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="10" groupid="9" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="73-10-32.7">73-10-32.7</xref>, Study regarding water losses, is repealed July 1, 2027.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="4-2" dnum="_-o:2-i" numlevel="1" lineno="33" slineno="2-4" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1001" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both">(2)</amend></display>Subsection <xref tempid="418">73-10g-607(5)</xref>, regarding a requirement to report to an interim <ln numlevel="1" lineno="34" slineno="2-5"/>committee, is repealed January 1, 2027.</subsection></section></bsec><bsec buid="1" num="73-10-32.7" type="enact" src="code" uid="C73-10-S32.7_2026050620260506" sort="73 10 00320720260506" numlevel="1" lineno="35" slineno="3-1" sn="3"><section numlevel="1" lineno="36" slineno="3-2" number="73-10-32.7" type="enact"><secline lineno="35">Section 3. Section <bold>73-10-32.7</bold> is enacted to read:</secline><catline lineno="36"><bold>73-10-32.7<parens><paren sort="00" type="original" show="true"><effect>Effective </effect><date>05/06/26</date></paren></parens>. Study regarding water losses.</bold></catline><subsection ssid="1-1" dnum="_-o:1-i" numlevel="1" lineno="37" slineno="3-3" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1" placement="noreturn"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1002" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(1)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="13" groupid="10" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">As used in this section:</amend><subsection ssid="1-2" dnum="_-o:a-i" numlevel="1" lineno="38" slineno="3-4" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1003" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="26" groupid="21" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">"Division" means the Division of Water Resources.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-3" dnum="_-o:b-i" numlevel="1" lineno="39" slineno="3-5" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1004" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="27" groupid="22" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">"Public water system" means the same as that term is defined in Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="19-4-102">19-4-102</xref>.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-4" dnum="_-o:2-i" numlevel="1" lineno="40" slineno="3-6" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1005" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(2)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="28" groupid="23" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">The division shall, in conjunction with the Division of Drinking Water, conduct a study <ln numlevel="1" lineno="41" slineno="3-7"/>regarding water loss by public water systems under which the division shall:</amend><subsection ssid="1-18" dnum="_-o:a-i" numlevel="1" lineno="42" slineno="3-8" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1006" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="98" groupid="79" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">compile and analyze water loss estimates based on system size from data provided by <ln numlevel="1" lineno="43" slineno="3-9"/>a public water system for the period beginning January 1, 2015, and ending <ln numlevel="1" lineno="44" slineno="3-10"/>December 31, 2024;</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-19" dnum="_-o:b-i" numlevel="1" lineno="45" slineno="3-11" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1007" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="104" groupid="84" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">provide an overview of industry standard water loss principles and practices, <ln numlevel="1" lineno="46" slineno="3-12"/>including for both public system and end use water losses; and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-20" dnum="_-o:c-i" numlevel="1" lineno="47" slineno="3-13" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1008" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(c)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="111" groupid="88" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">make recommendations on how to:</amend><subsection ssid="1-21" dnum="_-o:i-i" numlevel="1" lineno="48" slineno="3-14" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1009" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(i)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="116" groupid="92" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">improve water loss estimates and associated data reliability; and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-22" dnum="_-o:ii-i" numlevel="1" lineno="49" slineno="3-15" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1010" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(ii)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="121" groupid="96" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">reduce actual water losses.</amend></subsection></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-23" dnum="_-o:3-i" numlevel="1" lineno="50" slineno="3-16" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1011" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(3)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="126" groupid="100" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">The division shall report the division's findings under the study described in Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="73-10-32.7(2)"><ln numlevel="1" lineno="51" slineno="3-17"/>(2)</xref> to the Legislative Water Development Commission by no later than October 31, <ln numlevel="1" lineno="52" slineno="3-18"/>2026.</amend></subsection></section></bsec><bsec buid="5" type="uncod" untype="effdate" src="uncod" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" langlock="true" numlevel="1" lineno="53" slineno="4-1" sn="4"><section type="uncod" untype="effdate" display="false" src="uncod"><secline lineno="53">Section 4.  <bold>Effective Date.</bold></secline><subsection ssid="5-1" dnum="_-o:1-i" numlevel="1" lineno="54" slineno="4-2" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1" placement="noreturn"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1012" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(1)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="3" groupid="2" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" m-anum="0" m-ea="amend" m-pairid="5" m-groupid="4" m-style="1" m-owner="jchristopherson" m-level="1" amendtag="end">Except as provided in Subsection (2), this bill takes effect <effdate uid="code" date="5/6/2026">May 6, 2026</effdate>.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="5-2" dnum="_-o:2-i" numlevel="1" lineno="55" slineno="4-3" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1013" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(2)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="8" groupid="6" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">The actions affecting Section 63I-2-273 <parens><paren sort="00" type="original" show="true"><effect>Effective </effect><date>07/01/26</date></paren></parens> take effect on <effdate uid="code" date="7/1/2026">July 1, 2026</effdate>.</amend></subsection></section></bsec></bdy><foot><rev><tm>1-6-26 1:23 PM</tm></rev></foot></leg>